g.text: Supply ChainHow much of this product should we manufacture or procure? When should we start / stop manufacturing?How many of this item should we put on each shelf? In each warehouse?How should we manage our inventory and distribution?

FinanceHow likely is this product to succeed across our testing markets? How can we monitor these odds over time as we get new data?Does our expected demand justify our expenses and slotting fees? What budgetary constraints should we set?Dowehavethecapitalrequiredto keepupwithdemandifittakesoff?

Marketing & SalesWhichmarketsshouldwe launchin? Should we test-market before going big?How should we optimize our advertising and promotional spend within each market?How will we measure the health of our products and monitor cannibalization?How will we ensure compliance with pricing, promotion, and planogram agreements?
